name: Cosmella Tee and Poster
description:
Every year Coachella passes us by and people ask us if we're going to do a Coachella themed tee. We never did it, because it always seemed like a local Coachella Valley vendor's desperate attempt at a quick buck!  This year we decided we would do it, but instead of doing the usual cliche Coachella font play, or mountainous background and ferris wheel imagery we decided to do something a little different. We combined our love for Mad Magazine style parodies, and our general love of Mad magazine and combined it with the apparent hipster vibe of  Coachella to make our Mad inspired "Cosmella" mock Mad cover graphic. It features a very Hipster Alfred proudly wielding his $20 beer in a cheap plastic cup, a very original mustache that no one else has ever grown, Real-D glasses he swears are prescription, and Indian head band that proudly displays his affection for the Native Americans and a very stupid t-shirt with our original logo on it. How many of the 50 worst things about Coachella are just in our mock cover? Take a look and see for yourself. We don't hate or dislike anything about Golden Voice or the Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival. We just thought we'd take a kindhearted jab at one of our favorite local events here in the Coachella Valley!

Printed in very limited amounts and available just in time for Cosmella! This shirt includes an 11x17 poster of the shirt graphic and a post card sized invitation that includes a parody of the 2013 Coachella line up!
